headline: Expedia (NASDAQ:EXPE) Beats Expectations in Strong Q4 CY2025
summary: Online travel agency Expedia (NASDAQ:EXPE) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 11.4% year on year to $3.55 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($3.35 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 3.7% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.78 per share was 12.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Expedia: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The average estimate of eight analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $3.46 per share. The online travel company posted revenue of $3.55 billion in the period, also beating Street forecasts. Seven analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $3.4 billion.
